<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
This species was originally described, based on a single specimen collected by Y.M. Li from Taiyuan City, Shanxi Province in 1983 (Holotype: HBSU 2449, 
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, B" journalOrPublisher="Acta Mycologica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="208 - 217" refId="B28" refString="Liu, B, Du, F, Cao, JZ, 1985. New species and new combination of the genus Helvella. Acta Mycologica Sinica 4: 208 - 217" title="New species and new combination of the genus Helvella." volume="4" year="1985">Liu et al. 1985</bibRefCitation>
). Unfortunately, the type specimen was destroyed by a fire in MHSU in 1984 (
<bibRefCitation author="Cao, JZ" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" refId="B5" refString="Cao, JZ, 1988. The genus Helvella in China. MSc Thesis, Shanxi University, China." title="The genus Helvella in China. MSc Thesis, Shanxi University, China." year="1988">Cao 1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cao, JZ" journalOrPublisher="Acta Mycologica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="184 - 190" refId="B6" refString="Cao, JZ, Fan, L, Liu, B, 1990. Some new species and new records of the genus Helvella from China II. Acta Mycologica Sinica 9: 184 - 190" title="Some new species and new records of the genus Helvella from China II." volume="9" year="1990">Cao et al. 1990</bibRefCitation>
). To protect fungal collections after the fire, the remaining specimens, deposited in MHSU, were moved to HMAS. The neotype specimen HMAS 85689 was collected by the same collector as the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. taiyuanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="taiyuanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. taiyuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and identified by one of the original authors J.Z. Cao (
<bibRefCitation author="Cao, JZ" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" refId="B5" refString="Cao, JZ, 1988. The genus Helvella in China. MSc Thesis, Shanxi University, China." title="The genus Helvella in China. MSc Thesis, Shanxi University, China." year="1988">Cao 1988</bibRefCitation>
). Its detailed morphological characteristics are in accordance with the original description. We thus treat it as authentic material. As other specimens were neither cited in the protologue nor filed under this name, we thus designate HMAS 85689 as the neotype specimen of 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. taiyuanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="taiyuanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. taiyuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName class="Pezizomycetes" family="Helvellaceae" genus="Helvella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Helvella taiyuanensis" order="Pezizales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="taiyuanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Helvella taiyuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was once treated as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. solitaria" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="solitaria">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. solitaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Dissing, H" journalOrPublisher="Dansk Botanisk Arkiv" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 172" refId="B8" refString="Dissing, H, 1966. The genus Helvella in Europe, with special emphasis on the species found in Norden. Dansk Botanisk Arkiv 25: 1 - 172" title="The genus Helvella in Europe, with special emphasis on the species found in Norden." volume="25" year="1966">Dissing (1966)</bibRefCitation>
, based on morphological features (
<bibRefCitation author="Cao, JZ" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" refId="B5" refString="Cao, JZ, 1988. The genus Helvella in China. MSc Thesis, Shanxi University, China." title="The genus Helvella in China. MSc Thesis, Shanxi University, China." year="1988">Cao 1988</bibRefCitation>
), but the molecular differences between them are clear in the multigene analysis (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Bayesian phylogenetic tree of Helvella and Dissingia inferred from combined Hsp 90, ITS 2, LSU and TEF 1 dataset. Posterior probability values ≥ 0.90 (left) and bootstrap values ≥ 70 % (right) are indicated at nodes." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.60.38186.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352437" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" tableDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.60.38186.figure1">Figure 1</figureCitation>
). It should be a tenable species. The four specimens of the fungus examined are variable in colour of the hymenium and receptacle surface when dry or fresh, but stable in cupulate to saddle-shaped apothecia (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Helvella taiyuanensis a specimen sheet (HMAS 85689) b mature apothecia when dry (HMAS 85689) c mature apothecia when fresh (HMAS 254611) d mature apothecia when fresh (HMAS 277500) e mature apothecium when fresh (HMAS 279702) f-h ascospores in ascus (f, g: HMAS 85689, h: HMAS 254611). Scale bars: 0.8 cm (b, d); 2 cm (c); 20 μm (f), applies to g, h." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.60.38186.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352440" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" tableDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.60.38186.figure4">Figure 4</figureCitation>
). Phylogenetic analyses indicate that they belong to the same species (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Bayesian phylogenetic tree of Helvella and Dissingia inferred from combined Hsp 90, ITS 2, LSU and TEF 1 dataset. Posterior probability values ≥ 0.90 (left) and bootstrap values ≥ 70 % (right) are indicated at nodes." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.60.38186.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352437" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" tableDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.60.38186.figure1">Figures 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Maximum likelihood phylogeny of Helvellaceae inferred from combined LSU and TEF 1 dataset. Bootstrap values ≥ 50 % are indicated at nodes." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.60.38186.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352438" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" tableDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.60.38186.figure2">2</figureCitation>
and Suppl. material 1: S1-S4) although minor sequence divergences exist amongst collections. The maximum sequence divergences amongst collections are 1 bp in Hsp90, 6 bp in ITS2, 3 bp in LSU and 7 bp in TEF1.
</paragraph>
